      %h2.text-center Terms
      %p
        %strong Terms: Cocociti Rules
      %div We believe that everyone should have the power to create and share ideas and information instantly, without barriers. In order to protect the experience and safety of people who use Cocociti, there are some limitations on the type of content and behavior that we allow. All users must adhere to the policies set forth in the Cocociti Rules. Failure to do so may result in the temporary locking and/or permanent suspension of account(s). 
      %div  Please note that we may need to change these rules from time to time and reserve the right to do so. The most current version will always be available at cocociti.com/terms.
      %br
      %div
        %p
          %strong Content Boundaries and Use of Cocociti
        %p In order to provide the Cocociti service and the ability to communicate and stay connected with others, there are some limitations on the type of content that can be published with Cocociti.
        %div
          %strong Encryption & Content Privacy
          \: Connections to our website and app are secure and encrypted over HTTPS. All  user generated content, messages, comments, chats, and images are public by nature.
          %strong Trademark
          \: We reserve the right to reclaim usernames on behalf of businesses or individuals that hold legal claim or trademark on those usernames. Accounts using business names and/or logos to mislead others may be permanently suspended.
        %p
          %strong Copyright
          \: We will respond to clear and complete notices of alleged copyright infringement. Our copyright procedures are set forth in the Terms of Service.
        %p
          %strong Graphic content
          \: You may not use pornographic or excessively violent media in your profile image or header image. Cocociti may allow some forms of graphic content in wishes marked as sensitive media. When content crosses the line into gratuitous images of death, Cocociti may ask that you remove the content out of respect for the deceased.
        %p
          %strong Unlawful use
          \: You may not use our service for any unlawful purposes or in furtherance of illegal activities. International users agree to comply with all local laws regarding online conduct and acceptable content.
      %div
        %strong Misuse of Cocociti badges
        \: You may not use badges, such as but not limited to the “promoted” or “verified” Cocociti badge, unless provided by Cocociti. Accounts using these badges as part of profile photos, header photos, or in a way that falsely implies affiliation with Cocociti, may be suspended. 
      %div
        %p
          %strong Abusive Behavior
      %div We believe in freedom of expression and in speaking truth to power, but that means little as an underlying philosophy if voices are silenced because people are afraid to speak up. In order to ensure that people feel safe expressing diverse opinions and beliefs, we do not tolerate behavior that crosses the line into abuse, including behavior that harasses, intimidates, or uses fear to silence another user's voice.
      %div  
      %div Any accounts and related accounts engaging in the activities specified below may be temporarily locked and/or subject to permanent suspension.
      %div
        %p
          %strong Violent threats (direct or indirect)
          \: You may not make threats of violence or promote violence, including threatening or promoting terrorism.
        %p
          %strong Harassment
          \: You may not incite or engage in the targeted abuse or harassment of others. Some of the factors that we may consider when evaluating abusive behavior include:
        %p if a primary purpose of the reported account is to harass or send abusive messages to others;
        %p if the reported behavior is one-sided or includes threats;
        %p if the reported account is inciting others to harass another account; and
        %p if the reported account is sending harassing messages to an account from multiple accounts.
        %p
          %strong Hateful conduct
          \: You may not promote violence against or directly attack or threaten other people on the basis of race, ethnicity, national origin, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, religious affiliation, age, disability, or disease. We also do not allow accounts whose primary purpose is inciting harm towards others on the basis of these categories.
        %p
          %strong Multiple account abuse
          \: Creating multiple accounts with overlapping uses or in order to evade the temporary or permanent suspension of a separate account is not allowed.
        %p
          %strong Private information
          \: You may not publish or post other people's private and confidential information, such as credit card numbers, street address, or Social Security/National Identity numbers, without their express authorization and permission. In addition, you may not post intimate photos or videos that were taken or distributed without the subject's consent. Read more about our private information
          %a{href: "/privacy"} Policy
        %p
          %strong Impersonation
          \: You may not impersonate others through the Cocociti service in a manner that is intended to or does mislead, confuse, or deceive others. Read more about our impersonation policy here.
      %div
        %strong Self-harm
        \: You may encounter someone considering suicide or self harm on Cocociti. When we receive reports that a person is threatening suicide or self harm, we may take a number of steps to assist them, such as reaching out to that person expressing our concern and the concern of other users on Cocociti or providing resources such as contact information for our mental health partners.
      %div
        %p
          %strong Spam
        %p We strive to protect people on Cocociti from technical abuse and spam. Any accounts engaging in the activities specified below may be temporarily locked or subject to permanent suspension.
      %div
        %strong  
      %div
        %strong Username squatting
        \: You may not engage in username squatting. Accounts that are inactive for more than six months may also be removed without further notice. Some of the factors we take into consideration when determining what conduct is considered to be username squatting are:
      %div  
      %div the number of accounts created;
      %div  
      %ul
        %li creating accounts for the purpose of preventing others from using those account names;
        %li creating accounts for the purpose of selling those accounts; and
        %li using feeds of third-party content to update and maintain accounts under the names of those third parties.
        %li Invitation spam: You may not use Cocociti.com's address book contact import to send repeat, mass invitations.
        %li Selling usernames: You may not buy or sell Cocociti usernames.
      %div
        %p
          %strong Malware/Phishing
          \: You may not publish or link to malicious content intended to damage or disrupt another person’s browser or computer or to compromise a person’s privacy.
      %div  
      %div
        %strong Spam
        \: You may not use the Cocociti service for the purpose of spamming anyone. What constitutes “spamming” will evolve as we respond to new tricks and tactics by spammers. Some of the factors that we take into account when determining what conduct is considered to be spamming are:
      %div  
      %ul
        %li if you have followed and/or unfollowed large amounts of accounts in a short time period, particularly by automated means (aggressive following or follower churn);
        %li if you repeatedly follow and unfollow people, whether to build followers or to garner more attention for your profile;
        %li if your updates consist mainly of links, and not personal updates;
        %li if a large number of people are blocking you;
        %li if a large number of spam complaints have been filed against you;
        %li if you post duplicate content over multiple accounts or multiple duplicate updates on one account;
        %li if you post multiple unrelated updates to a topic using #, trending or popular topic, or promoted trend;
        %li if you send large numbers of duplicate replies or mentions;
        %li if you send large numbers of unsolicited replies or mentions;
        %li if you add a large number of unrelated users to lists;
        %li if you repeatedly create false or misleading content;
        %li if you are randomly or aggressively following, liking, or Rewishing wishes;
        %li if you repeatedly post other people’s account information as your own (bio, Wishes, URL, etc.);
        %li if you post misleading links (e.g. affiliate links, links to malware/clickjacking pages, etc.);
        %li if you are creating misleading accounts or account interactions;
        %li if you are selling or purchasing account interactions (such as selling or purchasing followers, Rewishes, likes, etc.); and
        %li
          if you are using or promoting third-party services or apps that claim to get you more followers (such as follower trains, sites promising "more followers fast", or any other site that offers to automatically add followers to your account).
          %br
          %br
      %div See our support articles on Following rules and best practices and Automation rules and best practices for more detailed information about how the Rules apply to those particular account behaviors. Accounts created to replace suspended accounts will be permanently suspended.
      %div  
      %div Accounts under investigation may be removed from search for quality. Cocociti reserves the right to immediately terminate your account without further notice in the event that, in its judgment, you violate these Rules or the Terms of Service.
      %div  
      %div  
      %div
        %div
          %strong Username Policy
        %div  
        %div
          %strong Inactive account policy
        %div
          %strong  
        %div What is Cocociti's inactive account policy?
        %div We encourage users to actively log in and use Cocociti when they register an account. To keep your account active, be sure to log in and share wishes on the platforms at least once in every 6 months. Accounts may be permanently removed due to prolonged inactivity. Please use your account once you sign up!
        %div  
        %div How does Cocociti determine inactivity?
        %div Inactivity is based on a combination of wish sharing and logging in. Please note that you may not be able to tell whether an account is currently inactive, as not all signs of account activity are publicly visible.
        %div  
        %div What if a potentially inactive account is using my registered trademark as its username or account name?
        %div If you believe your trademark rights are being infringed and the account seems inactive, please see Cocociti's trademark policy for additional information.
        %div  
        %div What if I have a request for a username from an account that looks inactive, but I don't have a registered trademark?
        %div We do not generally accept requests for usernames that seem inactive. If a username you would like is being used by an account that seems inactive, you should consider selecting an available variation for your use on Cocociti. In general, adding numbers, underscores, or abbreviations can help you come up with a great available username.
        %div  
        %div  
        %div
          %p
            %strong Username squatting policy
          %p Username squatting is prohibited by The Cocociti Rules.
        %div Please note that if an account has had no updates, no profile image, and there is no intent to mislead, it typically means there's no name-squatting or impersonation. Note that we will not release squatted usernames except in cases of trademark infringement. If your report involves trademark infringement, please consult those policies for instructions for reporting these accounts.
        %div
          %div  
      %div
        Attempts to sell, buy, or solicit other forms of payment in exchange for usernames are also violations and may result in permanent account suspension.
        %br
        %br
      %div
        %p
          %strong Private information posted on Cocociti
      %div Posting another person’s private and confidential information is a violation of the Cocociti Rules.
      %div  
      %div Some examples of private and confidential information include:
      %ul
        %li credit card information
        %li social security or other national identity numbers
        %li addresses or locations that are considered and treated as private
        %li non-public, personal phone numbers
        %li non-public, personal email addresses
        %li images or videos that are considered and treated as private under applicable laws
        %li intimate photos or videos that were taken or distributed without the subject's consent
      %div  
      %div Keep in mind that although you may consider certain information to be private, not all postings of such information may be a violation of this policy. We may consider the context and nature of the information posted, local privacy laws, and other case-specific facts when determining if this policy has been violated. For example, if information was previously posted or displayed elsewhere on the Internet prior to being put on Cocociti, it may not be a violation of this policy. 
      %div  
      %div
        %div
          %div  
          %div
            %strong The Chat Room Guidelines
          %div
            %strong  
          %div As a wish enablement platform and maintainers of this project, and in the interest of fostering an open and welcoming community, we pledge to respect all people who contribute through reporting spam, abuse, issues, posting feature requests, updating content, and other activities.
        %div
          %div We are committed to making participation on Cocociti chatrooms a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of level of experience, gender, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, personal appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, or nationality.
        %p Examples of unacceptable behavior by participants include:
        %ul
          %li The use of sexualized language or imagery
          %li Personal attacks
          %li Trolling or insulting/derogatory comments
          %li Public or private harassment
          %li Publishing other's private information, such as physical or electronic addresses, without explicit permission
          %li Other unethical or unprofessional conduct
        %div
          %div Cocociti and the admins have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject comments, features, images, issues, and other contributions that are not aligned to this Code of Conduct, or to ban temporarily or permanently any contributor for other behaviors that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.
        %div
          %div By adopting this Code of Conduct, users commit themselves to fairly and consistently applying these principles while engaging on Cocociti platform. Users who do not follow or enforce the Code of Conduct may be permanently removed from the chat rooms, chats and later from the platform itself.
        %div
          %div This Code of Conduct applies both within private chats, public chats, group chats, comments, wishes, chat rooms, spaces and elsewhere on Cocociti platform (including mobile & web) when an individual is representing the project or its community.
        %div
          %div Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported by writing to ayyo[at]cocociti.com or by contactacting the Cocociti support team. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated and will result in a response that is deemed necessary and appropriate to the circumstances. Users are obligated to maintain confidentiality with regard to the reporter of an incident.
          %div  
          %div These rules are not mandatory by imposed by the community and users while using the products and services of Cocociti. Cocociti reserves the right to ban, promote or demote users on it's web, mobile, online or offline platforms. Access to Cocociti is reserved and are in dole description of the company. Cocociti or it's employees cannot be held responsible for any of the damages; mental. physical, emotional inconveniences caused to you.
          %div  
          %div It is generally advised that you block abusive or spam users or any such content which is not welcome to you. The last thing you might do is to disable the account as this a voluntary platform and one is free to leave when they don;t like something about it.
          %div  
          %div Cocociti coins are both virtual and real. Company may withdraw the coins without prior notice and the coins will disappear from the user's wallet. Coin retention and withdrawals are subject to approvals. The coins bought or brought in by the customers won't disappear and in case of a discontinuity of the coins, these coins will ben refunded to the users depending on the number of coins available at the time of announcement.
          %div  
          %div
            %strong Following are the basic rules:
          %div  
          %ol
            %li Chat moderators are not necessarily Cocociti employees and could be users volunteering themselves to moderate/operate/supervise chat rooms and wish content to keep the Cocociti platform free from spam, abuse, hatred, unlawful conduct or anything that seem fit to the good standing of the Cocociti platform as set by the company in its terms, policies, and guidelines from time to time.
            %li Excessive offenders will be exempt from the warn/kick/ban rule & will be kicked/banned at the mods discretion.
            %li All Chat mods reserve the right to kick/ban a person if they feel it is necessary.
            %li Offensive, rude and unwanted behavior may cause you to get banned from this chat room without warning. (under any/all user names)
            %li The following topics should be avoided and can result in being banned from the room and/or chat server: Explicit sexual/pornographic talk, direct Violence towards other chatters, anything unconstitutional, racist comments and remarks.
            %li Any user can report spam, abuse or anything unacceptable by emailing at ayyo(at)cocociti.com and necessary action will be taken to help solve the issue by the quora time
            %li Spamming, flooding, excessive nick changes, excessive and annoying scripts, rudeness, name calling, harassing or threatening other chatters and rude or disruptive comments/actions will not be tolerated.
            %li Debates / arguments are ok, as long as they don't cause chaos, degrade others, or profanity directed at others. It will be up to the Ops to determine when an argument has gone beyond that point then all parties involved will be warned/kicked/banned.
            %li Impersonating another user is not allowed. Please use only your own name/username.
            %li If you are banned and continue to find ways in around the ban, this will result in dismissal of your account
            %li When being corrected by a moderator, please do not argue with them in the chat room. Instead, you may initiate a personal chat or write to us at ayyo(at)cocociti.com about it, however arguing in main chat is disruptive and causes a small situation to become a major one.
            %li Sharing any sensitive information in the chatrooms are not allowed. If you by accident share any suh information, you are advised to take the necessary steps to avoid the consequences. It applies not just to you, but to sharing information of anything in general. You are expected to behave responsibly.
            %li If you find yourself in trouble or distress due to ant Cocociti related reasons. You are advised to leave, take a break or write to us.
            %li Cocociti is a legal, healthy, and a happy platform where users come to wish, share hopes and experiences, seek help to fulfill wishes. Anything which goes against the community rules, conduct code, policies, guidelines, terms of the Cocociti will be taken action against.
            %li Cocociti holds the right to discontinue Coco coins or any functionalities/features on the platform without prior notice.
            %li Coin gifts are not mandatory for the help you provide. Each user can decide whether to give their coins or not.
            %li User donated coins & Cocociti donated coins can be dismissed by the company any time without a prior notice
          %div  
          %div  
          %div
            %strong Some more in detail
          %ol
            %li Post, promote, or distribute content that is illegal.
            %li Harass, threaten, embarrass, or do anything else to another chatter that is unwanted. This means: don't say bad things about them; don't attack their character, race, heritage, etc. If you disagree with someone, respond to the subject, not the person.
            %li Transmit or facilitate distribution of content that is harmful, abusive, racially or ethnically offensive, vulgar, sexually explicit, or in a reasonable person's view, objectionable. Community standards may vary, but there is no place in these rooms where hate speech is tolerated.
            %li Disrupt the flow of chat in chat rooms with vulgar language, abusiveness, hitting the return key repeatedly or inputting large streams of text so the screen goes by too fast to read, etc. This is online vandalism, and it ruins the experience for others.
            %li Pretend to be anyone whom you are not. You may not impersonate another user, a Cocociti Moderator, or a Cocociti employee
            %li The discussion of vulgar, illegal activities are not allowed 
            %li Foul language, will not be tolerated unless all letters of the word are replaced by substitute characters. Example ($#!^ is acceptable. Sh!t is not. In no way should there EVER be letters or numbers used.) Also prolific foul language use, such as \#*()$% ^!*()# *^() it all to \#@**, will not be tolerated either, regardless of covering up the entire word.
