        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        Overview
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        Generally, transactions are conducted smoothly on Cocociti. However there may be some cases where both the Buyers and Sellers may face issues. At Cocociti,
        we have a Dispute Resolution process in order to resolve disputes between Buyers and Sellers.
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        What is a 'dispute'?
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        A 'Dispute' can be defined as a disagreement between a Buyer and a Seller in connection with a transaction on the Website.
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        How does a 'dispute' occur in the Marketplace?
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        Disputes are filed as a result of a disagreement between the Buyer and the Seller. Disputes arise out of an issue that is raised by either party not being
        completely satisfied with the resolution of their complaint/issue.
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        It is important that before a Buyer/Seller raises a dispute, they should attempt to solve the issue. Please note that whenever a Buyer raises a dispute,
        the Seller's payment for that order is put on hold immediately until the issue is resolved.
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        How is a 'dispute' created?
        %p{:dir => "ltr"}
        Whenever there is a disagreement, the Owner/Buyer/Seller can write to hello@Cocociti.com, while the Seller can write to hello@Cocociti.com, in order to
        raise a dispute. Disputes can be raised at a particular transaction level.
        %br/
        %br/
